records.addlTxt:
9:06 AM Defendant Brandon T Dupee in court.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender. He is attempting to get court appointed counsel. Court notes that he does not qualify for court-appointed counsel and has reviewed the petition.
Court grants adjournment.
Final pre-trial scheduled for December 9, 2022 at 11:00 am.

10:03 AM Defendant Brandon T Dupee in court.  Prosecuting attorney Craig Lambert in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court questions defendant regarding counsel. 
Not guilty plea.
Final pre-trial scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 09:00 am.

10:46 AM Defendant Brandon T Dupee in court.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Court questions defendant regarding non-representation.
Matthew Scheffler appears by video, is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Zima. He is a police officer with the Marshfield Police Department. On 6/17/22, he executed a search warrant at a residence in the City of Marshfield. Defendant was at the residence at the time of the search. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. He searched defendant and found a plastic bag with a white substance in it. The substance tested positive for cocaine. Attorney Zima asks Court take judicial notice of Wood County Case 21CM642, a prior conviction for possession of cocaine.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bond is continued.
Arraignment scheduled for September 12, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on August 22, 2022 at 10:45 am.

11:58 AM Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Chris E.A. Framness Mr. in court for Brandon T Dupee. 
Defendant is requesting a continuance of the preliminary hearing. State does not object.
Court finds good cause to go outside time limits. Court grants adjournment. FPT will be set on 10/7/22 at 9:00 a.m. Bond is continued.
